The evidence with the title 'How much of federal spending is borrowed for every dollar ... ' says Jul 11, 2011  ... Today , 43 cents of every dollar spent is borrowed; this amount is about 4 times the rate in 1980 . Between 2007 and 2011 alone, the rate has increased 38 cents per dollar . At this pace, the historical trend of deficit spending continues at a distressing rate . The government ran a budget deficit in every year  ... 
